article.headline: Tennessee Tech 78, Austin Peay 74
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Milone Clark had 18 points and Tennessee Tech scored the last six points to beat Austin Peay 78-74 Tuesday night in the first round of the Ohio Valley Conference tourney. The Golden Eagles (18-11) will play Samford in the semifinals Friday in Nashville. Clark made a dunk to put Tennessee Tech ahead 75-74 with 47 seconds left. Anthony Fisher then made two free throws with 20 seconds left to make it 77-74. Austin Peay's Todd Babington missed a 3-pointer with six seconds left that would have tied it. Tech's Derek Stribling made a free throw for the final score. Amadi McKenzie added 16 points for the Golden Eagles, Fisher had 12 and Jonathan Jones had a double-double with 11 points and a game-high 10 rebounds. Austin Peay (17-14) was led by Drake Reed with 16 points, Derek Wright with 13, Zac Schlader with 12 and Maurice Hampton with 11. Tennessee Tech led 36-31 at the half and controlled the boards 44-23.
